header.gameNote: AARON'S AMERICAN ATHLETIC CONFERENCE WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINAL

videos.description: UConn's Kia Nurse is left wide open in the corner for 3 to add to the Huskies' lead.
videos.headline: Huskies ball movement sets up Nurse for 3

videos.description: Napheesa Collier grabs a rebound, makes the layup plus the foul to add to UConn's 26-0 run.
videos.headline: Collier completes the and-1

videos.description: Katie Lou Samuelson finishes a reverse layup just before the halftime buzzer as UConn out scores Cincinnati 26-0 in the 2nd quarter alone to take a 43-5 lead to the locker room.
videos.headline: Samuelson beats buzzer to cap 34-0 run

videos.description: Cincinnati's Shanice Johnson sinks a 3 early in the 3rd quarter for the Bearcats' first basket since the 4:39 mark in the 1st quarter.
videos.headline: Cincinnati ends UConn's 38-0 run with a 3

videos.description: UConn's Molly Bent excites her teammates on the bench after driving for an and-1 jump shot.
videos.headline: Bent banks in the and-1 jumper

videos.description: UConn head coach Geno Auriemma talks about the Huskies' great rebounding ability and how it was key for them to get Azura Stevens involved early.
videos.headline: Geno impressed with UConn's win over Cincinnati

videos.description: Rebecca Lobo, Kara Lawson and Adam Amin detail how UConn was able to dominate on both ends of the floor in win over Cincinnati.
videos.headline: UConn advances after dominant win
